      "content": "yeah, it's definitely gonna be a headache. the devs are pretty set on it though, because the compute cost for the current stateful setup is getting too high. \n\nthe `stateless_executor/handler.py` essentially just routes requests to a database for context instead of keeping it in local memory. once this goes live, the `AgentCore` environment won't be running anymore—it'll just be these single-shot execution calls. \n\nis there anything in the current `AgentCore` architecture that would be absolutely impossible to migrate, or is it just a matter of rewriting the handlers?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
